# Commit, Push, Deploy

When asked to save work, deploy, or sync to remote:

- Run `git status --short --branch`, review relevant `git diff`, and inspect recent `git log --oneline -5` before committing.
- Include all intended tracked and untracked files, but never commit secrets (`.env*`, credentials, tokens, key material) unless explicitly requested and confirmed safe.
- Use Conventional Commits: `type(optional-scope): concise imperative description`.
- After committing, run `git status --short --branch`; if the branch is ahead, push to the tracked remote.
- For production frontend checks, prefer the Git-triggered Vercel deployment after pushing `main`. Do not run a local Vercel deploy from a dirty tree unless explicitly requested.
- Verify Vercel with `npx vercel@latest ls <project>` until the new production deployment is `Ready` or `Error`.
- If deployment errors, inspect logs with `npx vercel@latest inspect <deployment-url> --logs`, fix the blocking issue in a new Conventional Commit, push again, and re-check Vercel.
- Report the pushed commit hash(es), deployment URL, final deployment status, and any files intentionally left uncommitted.
